.TH "zynqmp_dp_mode_configure" 9 "zynqmp_dp_mode_configure" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zynqmp_dp_mode_configure \- Configure the link values
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" zynqmp_dp_mode_configure
.BI "(struct zynqmp_dp *dp "  ","
.BI "int pclock "  ","
.BI "u8 current_bw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dp" 12
DisplayPort IP core structure
.IP "pclock" 12
pixel clock for requested display mode
.IP "current_bw" 12
current link rate
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find the link configuration values, rate and lane count for requested pixel
clock \fIpclock\fP. The \fIpclock\fP is stored in the mode to be used in other
functions later. The returned rate is downshifted from the current rate
\fIcurrent_bw\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Current link rate code, or -EINVAL.
